  "rationale": "<p>Choice B is correct. The slope is (0 &minus; 2)/(3 &minus; 0) = &minus;&frac23;, and the <i>y</i>-intercept is 2, giving <i>y</i> = &minus;&frac23;<i>x</i> + 2.</p><p>Choice A has the wrong sign for the slope. Choice C has the wrong <i>y</i>-intercept sign. Choice D inverts the slope magnitude.</p>",
